'''奈米碳管黑體'''（Vantablack）是目前已知最黑的物質之一，由垂直排列生成的[[奈米碳管|奈米碳管]]組成<ref name="SCMP">{{cite web| url=http://www.scmp.com/news/world/article/1554903/vantablack-worlds-darkest-material-unveiled-uk-firm| title=Vantablack, the world’s darkest material, is unveiled by UK firm| date=15 July 2014| website=South China Morning Post - World| accessdate=19 July 2014| archive-date=2016-07-01| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701140136/http://www.scmp.com/news/world/article/1554903/vantablack-worlds-darkest-material-unveiled-uk-firm| dead-url=no}}</ref>，常温下本体不发射可见光，而且吸收最高達99.965%的可見光波段電磁輻射。<ref name="NBCNews">{{cite web| url=http://www.nbcnews.com/science/science-news/vantablack-u-k-firm-shows-worlds-darkest-material-n155581| title=Vantablack: U.K. Firm Shows Off 'World's Darkest Material'| date=15 July 2014| website=NBCNews.com| accessdate=19 July 2014| archive-date=2015-12-09| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209071525/http://www.nbcnews.com/science/science-news/vantablack-u-k-firm-shows-worlds-darkest-material-n155581| dead-url=no}}</ref>因为當光線入射奈米碳管黑體時幾乎不會反射出去，而是會侷限於管壁之中不斷偏折，直到最後轉換成熱能為止。

==命名來源==
由「垂直排列之奈米碳管陣列」的英文'''V'''ertically '''A'''ligned '''N'''ano'''T'''ube '''A'''rrays的字母縮寫排列而成，後面再接英文的「黑」black，形成Vantablack，中文結合音意译為“梵塔黑”。<ref name="YahooCa">{{cite web|url=https://ca.news.yahoo.com/scientists-developed-black-deep-makes-3d-objects-look-233004466.html?pt=Array|title=Scientists have developed a black so deep it makes 3D objects look flat|author=Kuittinen, Tero|date=14 July 2014|website=Yahoo! News Canada|accessdate=19 July 2014|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303172537/https://ca.news.yahoo.com/scientists-developed-black-deep-makes-3d-objects-look-233004466.html?pt=Array|dead-url=no}}</ref>此名稱被[[英國|英國]]的Surrey NanoSystems有限公司作為該材料的商標。

==應用==
這物質有許多潛在的應用，包括防止{{le|雜散光|Stray light}}進入[[望遠鏡|望遠鏡]]，改良地球上和太空中的紅外線照相機的影像表現。<ref name="HuffPost">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/14/darkest-material-created-vantablack_n_5584338.html|title=This May Be The World's Darkest Material Yet|author=Howard, Jacqueline|date=14 July 2014|website=Huffington Post|accessdate=19 July 2014|archive-date=2016-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307121740/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/14/darkest-material-created-vantablack_n_5584338.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

薩里奈米系統公司首席技術長班兼森表示：<ref name="HuffPost"/>

{{quote|比如說，它可以減少雜散光，改進敏銳的望遠鏡看見最暗星的可行性... 它的極低反射率改良了地面、太空以及空中儀器的解析度。}}

奈米碳管黑體同時增加了[[聚光太陽能熱發電|聚光太陽能熱發電]]的熱吸收率，以及軍事應裡的熱迷彩。

這物質同時也被藝術家{{le|Anish Kapoor|Sir Anish Kapoor}}使用。他表示，「他就像顏料一樣有用...想像一下一個如此黑的空間，以致於當你漫步於其中時你無法感受你的位置、你的身分、特別是無從得知時間，你完全失去了這些感覺。」<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-29326916 |title=How black can black be? |date=23 September 2014 |accessdate=7 December 2014 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=BBC.col.uk |publisher=BBC News |archive-date=2015-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150806085452/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-29326916 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

然而這種黑色會徹底破壞衣服的特性。

